T1  - Interlocking Directorates as An Interorganizational Strategy: A Test of Critical Assumptions
AU  - Zajac, Edward J.
Y1  - 1988/06/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256558
DO  - 10.5465/256558
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 428
EP  - 438
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study which identified some critical assumptions underlying the view that interlocking directorates are vehicles for interorganizational coordination or control. A discussion is presented about types of interdependence and the effects of interdependence on organizational effectiveness. A list is presented of standard industrial classification codes for the firms studied. The author presents a comparison of the frequency of interlocking directorates in best-linked industry with a random sample of industries.
