T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 405
EP  - 417
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article assesses the construct of personal control in an organizational setting using a base model of personal control in organizations. The difference between control possessed and control desired is examined, and a discussion is presented about the measurement of contingent and noncontingent supervisory behaviors. The author presents the results of goodness of fit and Chi-square difference tests for null and modified models. The article focuses on the perceptions of supervisor's behavior by subordinates.
AB  - The article assesses the construct of personal control in an organizational setting using a base model of personal control in organizations. The difference between control possessed and control desired is examined, and a discussion is presented about the measurement of contingent and noncontingent supervisory behaviors. The author presents the results of goodness of fit and Chi-square difference tests for null and modified models. The article focuses on the perceptions of supervisor's behavior by subordinates.
