TY  - JOUR
T1  - Implementing Externally Induced Innovations: A Comparison of Rule-Bound and Autonomous Approaches
AU  - Marcus, Alfred A.
Y1  - 1988/06/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256547
DO  - 10.5465/256547
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 235
EP  - 256
VL  - 31
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This research analyzed how nuclear power plants implemented safety review innovations introduced by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission after the Three Mile Island accident. The findings suggested that nuclear power plants with relatively poor safety records tended to respond in a rule-bound manner that perpetuated their poor safety performance and that nuclear power plants whose safety records were relatively strong tended to retain their autonomy, a response that reinforced their strong safety performance.
AB  - This research analyzed how nuclear power plants implemented safety review innovations introduced by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission after the Three Mile Island accident. The findings suggested that nuclear power plants with relatively poor safety records tended to respond in a rule-bound manner that perpetuated their poor safety performance and that nuclear power plants whose safety records were relatively strong tended to retain their autonomy, a response that reinforced their strong safety performance.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/256547
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/256547
Y2  - 2026/04/24
